answerText: Australian Outback[10] This town in the Outback is situated at the geographical center of Australia. It is named after the wife of telegrapher Sir Charles Todd.

question: Question: Anna Hingley was the first woman to traverse this region on horseback, from Broome to Cairns. For 10 points each: [10] Name this arid region that covers seventy percent of Australia.
